      "card": {
        "oneLiner": "74F | CC: Fever, dysuria, left flank pain | Vitals: HR 112, BP 104/62, RR 22, SpO2 95%, T 38.9°C | ESI 2 — Suspected recurrent pyelonephritis/urosepsis with new confusion, mechanical mitral valve on warfarin, prior ESBL E. coli",
        "sections": [
          {
            "id": "approach",
            "title": "Things That Change My Approach",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Mechanical mitral valve (St. Jude 2015) + fever/rigors today → prosthetic valve endocarditis must stay on differential; prior TTE (2/2026) negative but explicitly noted limited sensitivity for prosthetic valve IE; blood cultures before antibiotics, consider TEE if bacteremic",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "dr-mo-echo-0217",
                    "label": "TTE 2/17/2026"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "bin-mo-pdf-id-fax",
                    "label": "ID consult fax 4/14/2026"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "proc-mo-mvr",
                    "label": "Surgical history — MVR 2015"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Prior admission 4/2026 for pyelonephritis with ESBL-producing E. coli resistant to ceftriaxone/cipro/levo/TMP-SMX; ID standing order: empiric carbapenem for any future febrile UTI, ceftriaxone expected to fail",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "dr-mo-ucx-0412",
                    "label": "Urine culture 4/12/2026"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "bin-mo-pdf-id-fax",
                    "label": "ID consult fax 4/14/2026"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "bin-mo-dcsum-0416",
                    "label": "Discharge summary 4/16/2026"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "New mild confusion this AM per daughter in patient documented cognitively intact at baseline (6/9/2026) — concerning for sepsis-associated encephalopathy, raises acuity beyond vitals alone",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "appt-margaret-okafor",
                    "label": "ED Triage 7/18/2026"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "soc-mo-living",
                    "label": "Living situation 6/9/2026"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "CKD stage 3b (eGFR ~34, Cr 1.6–1.7) — renal dosing required for carbapenem/aminoglycosides; nitrofurantoin contraindicated",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "cond-mo-ckd",
                    "label": "CKD stage 3b"
